(TMDB 5000 Movie Dataset)¶

by (Mo3az Elsokary)¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

This data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including popularity, budget, revenue, director, vote average, release year and more.

still there is some missing data in two major columns [ revenue_adj and budget_adj ] so that we should handle it wisely :

first i created a new column called income to represent the ratio between the revenue_adj and budget_adj and extracted the median that will use to extract the missing values ; then used np.where function to replace the missing values.

In [23]:
# the mean adjusted budget by director
mean_director_budget = data.groupby('director').budget_adj.mean()

# the mean popularity by director
mean_director_popularity = data.groupby('director').popularity.mean()

# the mean vote average by director
mean_director_vote = data.groupby('director').vote_average.mean()

#  the mean adjusted revenue by director
mean_director_revenue = data.groupby('director').revenue_adj.mean()

# the mean release year by director
mean_director_release_year = data.groupby('director').release_year.mean()

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

This cleaned data set contains information about 6,160 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including 6 columns ['popularity','directors','vote_average','release_year','budget_adj','revenue_adj']. and there is another special data created for answeing some quistions about directors and it contains 2958 different directors with 4 features of mean of ['budget_adj', 'popularity', 'revenue_adj', 'vote_average', 'release_year'].

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I'm most interested in figuring out the directors, popularity and revenue_adj.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

i will use the all other columns to answer a lot of questions about the intrested features.
